WEBVTT

00:02.401 --> 00:04.941
- [Gordon] I'm visiting
an inn in Massachusetts

00:04.941 --> 00:07.244
that's being run by a
dysfunctional couple.

00:07.244 --> 00:10.633
- I love you so much, but you
suck as a business partner.

00:10.633 --> 00:11.711
- [Gordon] He's lost...

00:11.711 --> 00:13.301
- I have no idea what I'm doing here.

00:13.301 --> 00:14.766
- [Gordon] And she's lost it.

00:14.766 --> 00:15.701
(sobs)

00:15.701 --> 00:17.710
- Just wanted to keep it together tonight.

00:17.710 --> 00:19.407
- And with the staff suffering as well...

00:19.407 --> 00:21.094
What's the worst thing
she's ever done to you?

00:21.094 --> 00:22.360
- Smacked me on the back of the head.

00:22.360 --> 00:24.633
- [Gordon] I'm not even sure
if I can get through to them.

00:24.633 --> 00:26.523
The whole operation is screwed.

00:26.523 --> 00:27.780
- What do you think we should do?

00:27.780 --> 00:28.613
- Close.

00:28.613 --> 00:30.363
- Have a nice night.

00:33.341 --> 00:36.008
(melodic music)

00:37.583 --> 00:39.869
- [Gordon] Nestled in the
heart of scenic New England

00:39.869 --> 00:42.235
lies the small industrial
town of Southbridge,

00:42.235 --> 00:43.402
Massachusetts.

00:45.421 --> 00:47.450
It's home to the Vienna
Inn and Restaurant.

00:47.450 --> 00:50.043
Husband and wife, Jonathan and Lisa Krach,

00:50.043 --> 00:51.715
have owned and operated the inn

00:51.715 --> 00:54.963
since buying the property
back in the year 2000.

00:54.963 --> 00:57.493
- Jonathan had this crazy idea

00:57.493 --> 01:01.883
of creating the Vienna
as an Austrian restaurant

01:01.883 --> 01:03.882
and bed-and-breakfast.

01:03.882 --> 01:06.725
- She said, "Have you been drinking?"

01:06.725 --> 01:09.262
I said, "No, not yet."

01:09.262 --> 01:12.403
- We try to transport
people and to give them

01:12.403 --> 01:14.445
that feeling of being in Vienna

01:14.445 --> 01:16.778
without having to fly there.

01:19.364 --> 01:22.035
- When people come in and they
stay here for the first time,

01:22.035 --> 01:24.659
they think that Jonathan and
Lisa are very gracious hosts.

01:24.659 --> 01:27.087
Charming, the perfect married couple.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.107
But if you dig a little bit deeper

01:29.107 --> 01:31.103
and you stay a little bit longer,

01:31.103 --> 01:33.146
you find out it's quite a different story.

01:33.146 --> 01:34.699
- Lisa is an emotional person.

01:34.699 --> 01:36.098
She does get upset often.

01:36.098 --> 01:38.202
She will just, you know, explode

01:38.202 --> 01:40.988
and she can't help but be upset.

01:40.988 --> 01:42.639
She's over the top.

01:42.639 --> 01:44.511
(snaps belt)

01:44.511 --> 01:47.106
- My beautiful wife, my boss,

01:47.106 --> 01:49.724
sometimes she's not so nice to me.

01:49.724 --> 01:53.107
- Why do you always have to
dress like a goddamn like bum?

01:53.107 --> 01:55.755
- There has been a time where
I called her a psycho bitch

01:55.755 --> 01:57.565
'cause she was being a psycho bitch.

01:57.565 --> 01:58.949
- Clean up, man.

01:58.949 --> 02:00.504
I'm done with this.

02:00.504 --> 02:02.420
- I don't feel like Lisa's authentic.

02:02.420 --> 02:05.169
When she's crying, I don't
feel like she ever means it.

02:05.169 --> 02:07.336
(sobbing)

02:09.640 --> 02:12.561
- Jonathan and Lisa live
in a room at the inn.

02:12.561 --> 02:14.217
You can hear them screaming at each other.

02:14.217 --> 02:15.744
You can hear it in the dining room.

02:15.744 --> 02:17.343
So there's no boundaries.

02:17.343 --> 02:19.480
They'll come down after the
shift at the end of the night,

02:19.480 --> 02:21.355
and they'll have cigars, have some drinks.

02:21.355 --> 02:23.977
The environment can quickly
become unprofessional.

02:23.977 --> 02:25.432
- She'll go up to a
table and ask them about,

02:25.432 --> 02:26.688
like, their sex lives.

02:26.688 --> 02:28.912
- You are good-looking.

02:28.912 --> 02:31.123
- We don't get that many
locals at the Vienna.

02:31.123 --> 02:34.148
There's, like, a lot of things
that people think in town

02:34.148 --> 02:35.368
about the Vienna,

02:35.368 --> 02:37.921
and I think it's become a little taboo.

02:37.921 --> 02:40.143
- You have those rumours going around.

02:40.143 --> 02:42.004
People say, "Ooh, the Vienna.

02:42.004 --> 02:43.090
They're all swingers.

02:43.090 --> 02:44.401
It's a big brothel."

02:44.401 --> 02:46.589
It's just ridiculous.

02:46.589 --> 02:48.746
It's ridiculous.

02:48.746 --> 02:52.296
- That being said, we're
very friendly people.

02:52.296 --> 02:53.463
Very friendly.

02:55.077 --> 02:57.685
(gentle music)

02:57.685 --> 02:59.849
- People from the outside
think the Vienna's

02:59.849 --> 03:02.311
doing very well and we're very prosperous,

03:02.311 --> 03:04.829
but somewhere in there, we're losing.

03:04.829 --> 03:06.559
- They're dragging us down with them,

03:06.559 --> 03:08.488
and if they want us to help them,

03:08.488 --> 03:10.238
they need to help us.

03:11.506 --> 03:15.740
- The Vienna is our home,
has been for 13-plus years.

03:15.740 --> 03:19.073
And, you know, it's hanging by a thread.

03:25.163 --> 03:27.913
(melodic music)

03:32.005 --> 03:34.228
- And this, 5:30 at table five.

03:34.228 --> 03:35.456
- He's walking right in.

03:35.456 --> 03:37.623
We wanna be ready for him.

03:38.625 --> 03:40.060
- Look at this place.

03:40.060 --> 03:41.031
My God.

03:41.031 --> 03:42.781
What happened to him?

03:43.866 --> 03:46.705
He didn't last very long, did he?

03:46.705 --> 03:49.288
- [Jonathan] He found our cat.

03:50.643 --> 03:52.156
- Well, bloody hell.

03:52.156 --> 03:53.736
Dead cat and a cabbage.

03:53.736 --> 03:55.319
- Isn't that funny?

03:56.166 --> 03:57.900
Hello, welcome.
- Good morning.

03:57.900 --> 03:59.038
Nice to meet you.

03:59.038 --> 03:59.871
- Likewise, good to see you too.

03:59.871 --> 04:00.704
Gordon.

04:00.704 --> 04:01.656
First name is?

04:01.656 --> 04:02.637
- Melissa.
- Melissa.

04:02.637 --> 04:03.668
- Good morning.

04:03.668 --> 04:04.501
How are you?
- How are you?

04:04.501 --> 04:05.334
Lisa Krach.

04:05.334 --> 04:06.167
- Lisa, nice to see you.

04:06.167 --> 04:07.275
You don't look very happy.

04:07.275 --> 04:08.608
- I do.

04:08.608 --> 04:10.545
It's my resting face.
- Oh, this is your happy face?

04:10.545 --> 04:11.500
- Wow.

04:11.500 --> 04:12.988
- Yes, welcome to the Vienna.

04:12.988 --> 04:14.032
- So happy to be here.

04:14.032 --> 04:15.470
What happened to the cat?

04:15.470 --> 04:16.526
(Lisa chuckles)

04:16.526 --> 04:17.358
Poor thing.

04:17.358 --> 04:18.493
- [Lisa] Cat got run over.

04:18.493 --> 04:19.326
- Oh, I see.

04:19.326 --> 04:20.658
And you got it stuffed?

04:20.658 --> 04:21.589
- [Lisa] For Halloween.

04:21.589 --> 04:22.548
- [Gordon] Right.

04:22.548 --> 04:25.672
- Actually, better to see you now.

04:25.672 --> 04:27.651
- Right, yeah.

04:27.651 --> 04:29.822
Love the attire, by the way.

04:29.822 --> 04:31.037
- Thank you.

04:31.037 --> 04:32.575
Everyone wears this.

04:32.575 --> 04:33.491
- Wow.

04:33.491 --> 04:34.886
How much are the outfits?

04:34.886 --> 04:36.442
- About $300, $400.

04:36.442 --> 04:37.303
- $300?

04:37.303 --> 04:38.650
- Average, you know.
- $300.

04:38.650 --> 04:39.645
They get their own.

04:39.645 --> 04:41.202
I mean, they're their
own dresses, you know?

04:41.202 --> 04:42.355
- Oh, you buy your own uniforms?

04:42.355 --> 04:43.188
- Yes.
- Yes, they do.

04:43.188 --> 04:44.021
- Stop it.

04:44.021 --> 04:44.854
- [Melissa] We do.

04:44.854 --> 04:45.998
- Well, they have 'em for many years.

04:45.998 --> 04:47.838
And it reminds them to not gain weight.

04:47.838 --> 04:49.915
(chuckles)

04:49.915 --> 04:51.954
- [Gordon] Wow, so who designed the place?

04:51.954 --> 04:53.921
- Well, my husband and I.

04:53.921 --> 04:56.738
- And whose idea was it to buy it?

04:56.738 --> 04:57.824
- My husband.

04:57.824 --> 04:58.913
- So it wasn't yours?

04:58.913 --> 04:59.969
- It was not my idea.

04:59.969 --> 05:01.626
I was actually very much against it.

05:01.626 --> 05:02.834
- Wow.

05:02.834 --> 05:04.258
Why were you against it?

05:04.258 --> 05:05.398
- It was very overwhelming.

05:05.398 --> 05:06.988
I had two small children.

05:06.988 --> 05:11.115
Probably, after I lost
my mind the first year...

05:11.115 --> 05:13.191
I think we started to get a hang of it.

05:13.191 --> 05:14.083
- And who's Austrian?

05:14.083 --> 05:14.916
Are you from-

05:14.916 --> 05:16.694
- My husband's half-Austrian and Polish.

05:16.694 --> 05:17.527
- Right.

05:17.527 --> 05:18.897
- I'm not nearly as exotic.

05:18.897 --> 05:19.933
I'm very American.

05:19.933 --> 05:21.545
- Right, and he's the chef, right?

05:21.545 --> 05:24.167
So he runs the restaurant,
kitchen, and you run the inn.

05:24.167 --> 05:25.000
- Correct.

05:25.000 --> 05:27.130
- [Gordon] And whose idea
was the violins on the table?

05:27.130 --> 05:28.136
- [Lisa] Mine.

05:28.136 --> 05:29.443
- [Gordon] Where'd that come from?

05:29.443 --> 05:31.979
- That was actually from an
estate sale down the street.

05:31.979 --> 05:33.515
- A dead man's violin?

05:33.515 --> 05:35.388
- Yeah, why not?

05:35.388 --> 05:37.947
- I don't wanna sit across
a table with my wife

05:37.947 --> 05:39.551
and look at a dead man's violin.

05:39.551 --> 05:40.384
- Well...

05:40.384 --> 05:41.389
- Bit freaky, no?

05:41.389 --> 05:42.222
- I don't know.

05:42.222 --> 05:43.981
What would you rather look
at when you see the Vienna?

05:43.981 --> 05:44.939
- Her.

05:44.939 --> 05:45.876
- Who's her?

05:45.876 --> 05:46.709
- My wife.

05:46.709 --> 05:48.031
- Oh, your wife, yes.

05:48.031 --> 05:52.086
But you have to have something
to make up that white space.

05:52.086 --> 05:53.951
What would you suggest?

05:53.951 --> 05:54.909
- My wife.

05:54.909 --> 05:55.932
(chuckles)

05:55.932 --> 05:57.179
- You gonna put her on the table?

05:57.179 --> 05:58.589
That's kind of scandalous.

05:58.589 --> 06:00.215
- I am so fucking confused.

06:00.215 --> 06:01.637
Dead man's violin.

06:01.637 --> 06:03.833
What about some flowers?

06:03.833 --> 06:08.833
Bloody hell, is this place
always as clustered as this?

06:09.248 --> 06:10.764
And who's that there?

06:10.764 --> 06:12.092
- A Prussian family, of course.

06:12.092 --> 06:16.048
That was Friedrich, that their
family all was murdered...

06:16.048 --> 06:16.881
- Murdered?

06:16.881 --> 06:17.714
- Yes.

06:17.714 --> 06:20.627
- Wow, so dead man's violin,
murderer on the wall.

06:20.627 --> 06:24.095
Great story to encourage a
nice, warm, welcoming dinner.

06:24.095 --> 06:26.977
So why don't I check in upstairs?

06:26.977 --> 06:28.401
- You can do that right now.

06:28.401 --> 06:29.234
- Yes, please.

06:29.234 --> 06:30.067
Yeah why not?

06:30.067 --> 06:30.900
Thank you.

06:30.900 --> 06:32.317
- You're welcome.

06:34.615 --> 06:35.517
- Wow.

06:35.517 --> 06:36.723
Interesting indeed.

06:36.723 --> 06:37.707
Just a clutter.

06:37.707 --> 06:39.188
- [Lisa] Your bedroom's over here.

06:39.188 --> 06:40.146
- [Gordon] Rocking chair?

06:40.146 --> 06:40.979
Where's that from?

06:40.979 --> 06:43.223
- That's actually the first
piece I ever refinished.

06:43.223 --> 06:44.339
- Wow.

06:44.339 --> 06:46.684
So you're quite an antiques hoarder.

06:46.684 --> 06:47.918
(knock at door)

06:47.918 --> 06:48.961
- [Val] Room service.

06:48.961 --> 06:49.957
- Oh, room service.

06:49.957 --> 06:50.915
Come in.

06:50.915 --> 06:51.995
Holy mackerel.

06:51.995 --> 06:54.180
- Now, what we have here
is some pulled boar.

06:54.180 --> 06:55.013
- Shredded.

06:55.013 --> 06:56.124
Shredded.
- Oh, pulled.

06:56.124 --> 06:58.126
- And then you have a little
celery root right on top.

06:58.126 --> 06:59.209
- [Gordon] Wow.

06:59.209 --> 07:00.156
And what's that?

07:00.156 --> 07:01.957
- [Lisa] It's a little parsley.

07:01.957 --> 07:03.040
- Excellent.

07:04.577 --> 07:05.474
Take one.

07:05.474 --> 07:06.880
- Would you like me to have one?

07:06.880 --> 07:07.713
- Yeah, of course.

07:07.713 --> 07:08.999
There's three pieces.

07:08.999 --> 07:09.957
Excellent.
- Okay.

07:09.957 --> 07:10.790
- Sure.

07:10.790 --> 07:11.748
- Thank you.

07:11.748 --> 07:12.666
- Thank you for sharing.

07:12.666 --> 07:13.624
- You're welcome.

07:13.624 --> 07:14.457
Hold on.

07:14.457 --> 07:15.290
Wait, wait.

07:15.290 --> 07:16.123
Let me put a little bit
of the garnish on there...

07:16.123 --> 07:17.013
- You want me to have that?

07:17.013 --> 07:20.263
- Yeah, we'll have a little piece each.

07:28.696 --> 07:31.444
What did you think of that, by the way?

07:31.444 --> 07:34.077
- Celery root, really don't like it.

07:34.077 --> 07:37.366
The pulled boar, maybe
just a bit more salt.

07:37.366 --> 07:38.199
- Wow.

07:38.199 --> 07:39.079
And what did you think of that?

07:39.079 --> 07:40.822
- I think it's a nice
little surprise for people

07:40.822 --> 07:44.246
when they come in to
liven up their appetite.

07:44.246 --> 07:45.770
- [Gordon] Boar was very watery.

07:45.770 --> 07:46.850
- It was very watery.

07:46.850 --> 07:47.767
I did notice that.

07:47.767 --> 07:49.823
- And the bread was soggy, soaking wet.

07:49.823 --> 07:51.255
- From the celery root.

07:51.255 --> 07:52.213
- [Gordon] Thank you.

07:52.213 --> 07:53.380
- Enjoy your stay.

07:53.380 --> 07:55.465
- Please pass on my comments to the chef.

07:55.465 --> 07:57.132
- I definitely will.

07:58.617 --> 07:59.700
- Here we go.

08:01.620 --> 08:02.673
- [Gordon] Oh, dear.

08:02.673 --> 08:03.506
Okay.

08:03.506 --> 08:04.339
Wow.

08:04.339 --> 08:05.613
And who designed these bedrooms?

08:05.613 --> 08:07.418
- I designed everything.

08:07.418 --> 08:08.468
- You designed?

08:08.468 --> 08:09.301
- Mm-hmm.

08:09.301 --> 08:10.834
I wallpapered it as well.

08:10.834 --> 08:12.223
- Seriously?

08:12.223 --> 08:13.823
What's this?

08:13.823 --> 08:15.526
- [Lisa] That's another closet.

08:15.526 --> 08:16.844
- What do you mean, another closet?

08:16.844 --> 08:18.358
- I don't have a closet in my bedroom.

08:18.358 --> 08:20.609
That's the closet that we
have because there's an area

08:20.609 --> 08:22.333
over here for guests to use.

08:22.333 --> 08:24.256
- But where am I gonna hang my clothes?

08:24.256 --> 08:25.756
- Right over here.

08:28.754 --> 08:29.587
- But...

08:31.333 --> 08:33.335
- You don't need an entire closet.

08:33.335 --> 08:35.687
- So if you need clothes
out of your closet

08:35.687 --> 08:37.477
you come in my bedroom?
- I have to plan ahead.

08:37.477 --> 08:39.017
Do you have the key on you?

08:39.017 --> 08:39.850
- I do.

08:39.850 --> 08:40.907
- Can I see inside?

08:40.907 --> 08:43.220
I just, I'm a bit freaked with
locked doors in my bedroom.

08:43.220 --> 08:44.053
- Gosh.

08:44.053 --> 08:45.200
- Yeah, I'm sorry.

08:45.200 --> 08:46.329
Thank you.
- It's okay.

08:46.329 --> 08:47.197
- It's right here.

08:47.197 --> 08:48.222
- Oh, it's there?

08:48.222 --> 08:49.055
Wow.

08:50.805 --> 08:53.244
(chuckles)

08:53.244 --> 08:54.737
- [Lisa] Just my closet.

08:54.737 --> 08:56.130
- Holy crap.

08:56.130 --> 08:57.399
Stop it.
- Yeah.

08:57.399 --> 08:58.232
- Stop it?

08:58.232 --> 08:59.084
- Seriously?

08:59.084 --> 09:00.485
- [Lisa] All my stuff.

09:00.485 --> 09:02.765
- [Gordon] It's like a
garage sale in a closet.

09:02.765 --> 09:04.270
- [Lisa] That's why we keep a lock on it.

09:04.270 --> 09:05.906
- I've got no interest in
wearing any of the garments,

09:05.906 --> 09:07.071
but thank you.

09:07.071 --> 09:07.904
- [Lisa] You sure?

09:07.904 --> 09:09.117
- I'm positive.

09:09.117 --> 09:10.462
100% positive.

09:10.462 --> 09:12.223
Bloody hell.

09:12.223 --> 09:13.895
What's the price of this room?

09:13.895 --> 09:14.989
- [Lisa] This one is 220.

09:14.989 --> 09:16.570
- $220.

09:16.570 --> 09:17.678
Yeah?
- Correct.

09:17.678 --> 09:20.816
And I have to share my
wardrobe with the owner.

09:20.816 --> 09:22.468
What's through this room here?

09:22.468 --> 09:24.602
- [Lisa] That actually goes to my bedroom.

09:24.602 --> 09:25.718
- [Gordon] So do you just walk in

09:25.718 --> 09:27.474
when you need to get some clothes?

09:27.474 --> 09:28.307
- From here?

09:28.307 --> 09:30.530
- No, but from your bedroom to my bedroom.

09:30.530 --> 09:34.392
- [Lisa] Well, I only do
that once or twice a week.

09:34.392 --> 09:35.892
- And what's this?

09:37.058 --> 09:38.174
Wow.

09:38.174 --> 09:40.295
- It's an antique purse that was actually

09:40.295 --> 09:41.668
found in the house,

09:41.668 --> 09:44.916
and we thought it was really
neat to be able to have.

09:44.916 --> 09:47.194
That's a toothbrush
holder in case you decide

09:47.194 --> 09:48.593
to take it along with you.

09:48.593 --> 09:49.842
- That's a toothbrush holder?

09:49.842 --> 09:51.086
- Or you could stick tampons in there

09:51.086 --> 09:53.107
if you really wanted to.

09:53.107 --> 09:54.535
We do usually have those...

09:54.535 --> 09:55.793
Oh, they're not in there right now.

09:55.793 --> 09:56.626
There you go.

09:56.626 --> 09:57.857
- [Gordon] It's an old lady's case.

09:57.857 --> 09:59.765
- Mm-hmm, just trying
to think of clever ideas

09:59.765 --> 10:03.103
to make this feel like a historic inn.

10:03.103 --> 10:04.311
- Historic.

10:04.311 --> 10:05.188
- Mm.

10:05.188 --> 10:06.715
- It's definitely historic.

10:06.715 --> 10:07.798
Oh.

10:07.798 --> 10:08.773
Bloody hell.

10:08.773 --> 10:09.770
How old is that?

10:09.770 --> 10:10.728
- You need that?

10:10.728 --> 10:12.702
- No, just fascinated to
see what's in my basket.

10:12.702 --> 10:14.068
Thank you for that.

10:14.068 --> 10:15.026
Oh, dear.

10:15.026 --> 10:16.262
Everything looks dated.

10:16.262 --> 10:19.831
I mean, first impressions,
it looks very, very tired.

10:19.831 --> 10:21.180
What is all that?

10:21.180 --> 10:23.635
- [Lisa] That's if somebody
wants to throw roses on the bed.

10:23.635 --> 10:24.898
- [Gordon] Oh, for God's sake.

10:24.898 --> 10:26.480
- [Lisa] Isn't that adorable?

10:26.480 --> 10:28.704
- And then they go back in the drawer

10:28.704 --> 10:31.621
once you've used them.
- I guess so.

10:32.642 --> 10:35.146
Okay, well, I'll look forward
to seeing you downstairs.

10:35.146 --> 10:35.991
I'll have lunch.

10:35.991 --> 10:36.824
- Super.

10:36.824 --> 10:37.657
- Thank you.

