32:47.726 --> 32:50.366
When I had mentioned the Vienna, they say,

32:50.366 --> 32:53.106
"That's where the swingers go."

32:53.106 --> 32:56.667
You eat downstairs, and
then you go upstairs

32:56.667 --> 32:58.250
is what I was told.

32:59.897 --> 33:02.147
- [Gordon] But you've heard this before?

33:02.147 --> 33:04.861
- We've heard it for 13 years.

33:04.861 --> 33:06.958
- But is this due to
your late-night drinking

33:06.958 --> 33:07.890
and the partying?

33:07.890 --> 33:08.859
- I don't think so.

33:08.859 --> 33:10.405
- [Man] Fact or not, that's
how we see it, you know.

33:10.405 --> 33:12.012
- Yeah, cause you're living there.

33:12.012 --> 33:14.587
But what I'm trying to say is
that there are no boundaries.

33:14.587 --> 33:17.422
It's an oasis down there
that has got a Jacuzzi,

33:17.422 --> 33:20.309
a massage table, and if
the word has gotten out

33:20.309 --> 33:23.196
around town and then you're...

33:23.196 --> 33:25.016
- People misunderstood that room,

33:25.016 --> 33:26.264
and that's where it all started.

33:26.264 --> 33:29.431
- I'm just saying, it's either a business,

33:29.431 --> 33:30.721
or it's your home.

33:30.721 --> 33:32.304
There's no crossover.

33:32.304 --> 33:34.571
The mixed messages you're sending

33:34.571 --> 33:38.654
is your own fault 'cause
you haven't been clear.

33:39.568 --> 33:41.546
- I used to come to the restaurant

33:41.546 --> 33:43.417
probably every month or so,

33:43.417 --> 33:46.078
and I can tell you have a lot of, like,

33:46.078 --> 33:47.792
passion for your heritage,

33:47.792 --> 33:50.659
but it's not in the food anymore.

33:50.659 --> 33:53.582
If Gordon can help you take your heritage

33:53.582 --> 33:55.839
and the food and modernise it

33:55.839 --> 33:57.477
and you can progress with that,

33:57.477 --> 33:58.408
I'll come every Friday.

33:58.408 --> 33:59.241
Mark my words.

33:59.241 --> 34:00.824
It's a promise.

34:00.824 --> 34:03.864
- Do you have anything to say,
both of you, to these guests?

34:03.864 --> 34:07.590
- Thank you so much for
your honesty and input, and,

34:07.590 --> 34:09.367
really, really appreciate it.

34:09.367 --> 34:12.065
We're gonna be making some big changes

34:12.065 --> 34:16.143
to address many of the
things you talked about.

34:16.143 --> 34:19.032
- The staff have been incredibly loyal.

34:19.032 --> 34:20.572
They haven't been treated the way

34:20.572 --> 34:22.255
they should have been treated.

34:22.255 --> 34:24.277
I'm undecided about these two,

34:24.277 --> 34:26.136
but I am committed to that team,

34:26.136 --> 34:28.150
'cause I see what is at stake

34:28.150 --> 34:31.021
and the jeopardy they face going forward.

34:31.021 --> 34:35.603
Now I've got something
else important to sort out.

34:35.603 --> 34:38.187
(upbeat music)

34:39.800 --> 34:41.520
After leaving Jonathan and Lisa,

34:41.520 --> 34:44.735
I moved forward with my plans
to help renovate the inn.

34:44.735 --> 34:46.744
I brought in sommelier Dave Foss

34:46.744 --> 34:48.437
to create a beverage programme...

34:48.437 --> 34:49.882
Just have a look in here.

34:49.882 --> 34:50.715
I mean...

34:50.715 --> 34:51.994
- That wine's fantastic.

34:51.994 --> 34:54.300
- [Gordon] From the excessive
inventory they weren't using.

34:54.300 --> 34:55.132
- '03.

34:55.132 --> 34:56.480
Oh, that's delicious.

34:56.480 --> 34:58.438
- [Gordon] My team worked
up to the last minute

34:58.438 --> 35:01.661
transforming the many
spaces at the Vienna.

35:01.661 --> 35:02.673
- Wow.

35:02.673 --> 35:03.536
Oh-ho.

35:03.536 --> 35:04.369
- [Man] Wow.

35:04.369 --> 35:05.620
That is amazing.

35:05.620 --> 35:06.902
- Holy smokes.

35:06.902 --> 35:08.700
This is beautiful.

35:08.700 --> 35:11.064
This is incredible.

35:11.064 --> 35:12.314
Bravo.

35:12.314 --> 35:14.910
- The Vienna had no
organisation for managing

35:14.910 --> 35:16.810
their day-to-day operations.

35:16.810 --> 35:18.863
So I gave them a state-of-the-art system

35:18.863 --> 35:21.704
to help with all their
hotel operational needs.

35:21.704 --> 35:25.053
Welcome to the WebRezPro system.

35:25.053 --> 35:27.649
And this will help
transform your business.

35:27.649 --> 35:29.703
It will link up to the POS system,

35:29.703 --> 35:32.398
and it will give you data
like you've never had before.

35:32.398 --> 35:33.231
- Fabulous.

35:33.231 --> 35:36.828
- You need to be organised,
from the inventories

35:36.828 --> 35:39.537
to the wage costs to the salaries

35:39.537 --> 35:42.083
to the POS systems to the checking-in

35:42.083 --> 35:44.514
and the checking-out system.

35:44.514 --> 35:47.445
And the good news, guests
can now book online.

35:47.445 --> 35:50.695
So this should relieve a huge headache.

35:52.121 --> 35:54.052
I could see that everyone was thrilled

35:54.052 --> 35:55.668
with the changes at the Vienna.

35:55.668 --> 35:56.501
Good.

35:56.501 --> 35:57.455
Have a good look round.

35:57.455 --> 35:58.929
But as I watched Lisa...

35:58.929 --> 36:00.622
- Where's this stuff from?

36:00.622 --> 36:02.336
- [Gordon] I noticed she was dissatisfied

36:02.336 --> 36:03.657
with the renovations.

36:03.657 --> 36:05.142
- These are different
chairs from the other ones,

36:05.142 --> 36:06.475
aren't they?

36:06.475 --> 36:09.330
I was just seeing if it was 100% cotton.

36:09.330 --> 36:10.653
Is that a pull-out?

36:10.653 --> 36:12.758
- No, it doesn't need to be a pull-out.

36:12.758 --> 36:15.996
And right now I'm worried
where Lisa's head is,

36:15.996 --> 36:18.829
going into relaunch this evening.

36:25.934 --> 36:27.186
Good evening!
- Good evening.

36:27.186 --> 36:28.369
- I can help you with your bags.

36:28.369 --> 36:29.593
First let's get you checked in.

36:29.593 --> 36:30.652
- [Gordon] While it was time to relaunch

36:30.652 --> 36:31.875
the inn and restaurant...

36:31.875 --> 36:33.447
- Little more modern.

36:33.447 --> 36:34.510
- We have an order.

36:34.510 --> 36:36.945
- [Gordon] I provided the
staff with brand-new uniforms

36:36.945 --> 36:39.120
that go with the new updated menu

36:39.120 --> 36:42.004
that includes wine
pairing and beer flights.

36:42.004 --> 36:44.039
- First is going to be the grapefruit,

36:44.039 --> 36:46.245
then the second is
going to be the pilsner.

36:46.245 --> 36:47.398
- These are up here.

36:47.398 --> 36:49.101
- Please get out of here, Lisa.

36:49.101 --> 36:50.428
Off the line.

36:50.428 --> 36:53.178
- Shall I just turn this lamp on?

36:55.001 --> 36:56.345
No light bulb.

36:56.345 --> 36:57.412
(chuckles)

36:57.412 --> 36:58.245
Oops.

36:59.120 --> 37:00.001
Excuse me.

37:00.001 --> 37:01.215
- [Gordon] What's wrong?

37:01.215 --> 37:02.275
- No light bulb in there.

37:02.275 --> 37:03.450
I just wanna turn that light on.

37:03.450 --> 37:04.797
- Don't worry about it.

37:04.797 --> 37:06.460
Who's complaining about the light bulb?

37:06.460 --> 37:08.360
- Oh, just making sure that
they have enough light.

37:08.360 --> 37:10.413
Trying to turn it on,
then realised it later.

37:10.413 --> 37:11.381
- Doesn't matter.

37:11.381 --> 37:12.412
It doesn't matter.

37:12.412 --> 37:13.722
Let's focus on the big things.

37:13.722 --> 37:16.253
Are you always like this over
little details like that?

37:16.253 --> 37:18.888
- I like to have things
feel right, and so...

37:18.888 --> 37:21.056
I'm feeling extra, like, an extra need

37:21.056 --> 37:23.375
to make sure everything's
right, that's all.

37:23.375 --> 37:24.208
- OTT.

37:24.208 --> 37:25.103
- Just a fusser.

37:25.103 --> 37:26.061
- OTT.

37:26.061 --> 37:26.920
- Probably.

37:26.920 --> 37:28.079
Whatever that means.

37:28.079 --> 37:29.294
- Over the top.

37:29.294 --> 37:30.181
Over the top.

37:30.181 --> 37:31.200
- Well, I guess I don't have to be

37:31.200 --> 37:32.618
so over the top now, do I?

37:32.618 --> 37:34.213
- You do not.

37:34.213 --> 37:35.296
Jesus Christ.

37:41.181 --> 37:43.046
What is wrong with her tonight?

37:43.046 --> 37:44.129
Do you think she's gonna go back

37:44.129 --> 37:45.412
to her old ways when I leave?

37:45.412 --> 37:47.008
- [Melissa] She might accidentally.

37:47.008 --> 37:48.260
- Customer's coming.

37:48.260 --> 37:49.093
Welcome.

37:49.093 --> 37:51.787
While Lisa is nitpicking
everything unnecessarily...

37:51.787 --> 37:54.222
- [Jessica] Do you guys have
the appetiser for table five?

37:54.222 --> 37:55.055
- Oh, sorry.

37:55.055 --> 37:55.888
- [Jonathan] We didn't give you that yet?

37:55.888 --> 37:56.846
- [Jessica] No, you didn't.

37:56.846 --> 37:57.679
- No?

37:57.679 --> 37:58.512
- [Jessica] No.

37:58.512 --> 38:00.279
- [Gordon] Jonathan is
lost in the kitchen,

38:00.279 --> 38:02.744
and service is starting to suffer.

38:02.744 --> 38:04.563
What table number's this, please?

38:04.563 --> 38:05.746
- That is table number 11.

38:05.746 --> 38:06.998
They're waiting on two
flank steaks with it.

38:06.998 --> 38:08.412
- Where's the flank steak?

38:08.412 --> 38:09.370
Are they coming?

38:09.370 --> 38:10.203
- Moments.

38:10.203 --> 38:11.286
Moments.

38:11.286 --> 38:12.119
Minutes.

38:12.119 --> 38:13.310
- Who's cooking the flank steak?

38:13.310 --> 38:15.534
Come on, guys, we can do one
four-top at the same time, yes?

38:15.534 --> 38:17.935
I designed the menu around
the size of the kitchen,

38:17.935 --> 38:21.685
the speed of both you
working together, okay?

38:22.986 --> 38:24.734
Come back for the flank.

38:24.734 --> 38:26.223
- What the hell is this?

38:26.223 --> 38:28.009
- Look at me, both of you, both of you.

38:28.009 --> 38:29.501
Cut the shit, okay?

38:29.501 --> 38:30.334
Look at me.

38:30.334 --> 38:32.247
You're more than capable of
doing four fucking main courses

38:32.247 --> 38:33.428
at the same time,

38:33.428 --> 38:34.945
especially when there's two of you.

38:34.945 --> 38:37.064
And one of those main
courses is the same dish.

38:37.064 --> 38:38.317
We've gotta talk to each other,

38:38.317 --> 38:39.894
but I'm not gonna start
sending one dish at a time

38:39.894 --> 38:40.977
for a four-top.

38:40.977 --> 38:41.810
- Serious?

38:41.810 --> 38:42.643
- Doesn't matter.

38:42.643 --> 38:44.942
It doesn't matter at all.

38:44.942 --> 38:46.750
- Jonathan, hey, look at me.

38:46.750 --> 38:47.583
Look at me.

38:47.583 --> 38:49.132
I need some fucking effort
from you a little bit.

38:49.132 --> 38:50.239
I need a little bit of respect,

38:50.239 --> 38:51.631
a little bit of effort from you, okay?

38:51.631 --> 38:52.635
Yeah, and look at me.

38:52.635 --> 38:54.337
You're the man holding this
fucking thing together.

38:54.337 --> 38:56.678
If you go down, the whole
fucking place is gonna go down.

38:56.678 --> 38:58.275
I need you to step up, okay?

38:58.275 --> 38:59.593
I need you to talk a little bit.

38:59.593 --> 39:02.573
And I want four main courses
at the same fucking time.

39:02.573 --> 39:03.406
- Oh, dear God.

39:03.406 --> 39:04.239
- [Gordon] Jonathan.

39:04.239 --> 39:05.072
- Yes?

39:05.072 --> 39:06.780
- You can get your mind set
around four main courses

39:06.780 --> 39:07.863
at the same fucking time.

39:08.831 --> 39:11.857
(melodic music)

39:11.857 --> 39:13.991
Understand, we're serving
one table at a time,

39:13.991 --> 39:15.612
and we're gonna complete that table,

39:15.612 --> 39:18.203
four main courses, three main
courses, five main courses.

39:18.203 --> 39:19.323
We're gonna talk together.

39:19.323 --> 39:20.986
- Sausage goes with what, the two soups?

39:20.986 --> 39:22.340
- What's coming next?

39:22.340 --> 39:24.762
- It's gonna be sausage, two carrot soups,

39:24.762 --> 39:25.919
and a fried cheese.

39:25.919 --> 39:26.752
- Good.

39:26.752 --> 39:27.748
- For table seven.

39:27.748 --> 39:28.955
- Okay, so we're talking now.

39:28.955 --> 39:29.824
- Yep.
- Good.

39:29.824 --> 39:30.657
- Carrot?

39:30.657 --> 39:31.763
- Thank you very much.

39:31.763 --> 39:33.188
- I have your flank steaks.

39:33.188 --> 39:35.354
Your wine is coming right away, okay?

39:35.354 --> 39:36.935
- Your sausage.

39:36.935 --> 39:38.519
You guys are all sharing, right?

39:38.519 --> 39:39.504
- Yes.
- Yeah.

39:39.504 --> 39:41.210
- [Jessica] I think the
new Vienna will definitely

39:41.210 --> 39:43.080
attract a younger crowd.

39:43.080 --> 39:44.222
- Oh, my God.

39:44.222 --> 39:45.484
- So beautiful.

39:45.484 --> 39:47.793
- I'm super excited about the new changes,

39:47.793 --> 39:49.779
and I hope they'll last.

39:49.779 --> 39:50.779
I really do.

39:52.468 --> 39:53.381
- Right.

39:53.381 --> 39:57.696
We've had ups and downs, but
tonight is a prime example

39:57.696 --> 40:01.635
of how good and how profitable
this business can be.

40:01.635 --> 40:03.109
Customers loving the food.

40:03.109 --> 40:04.431
They love the decor.

40:04.431 --> 40:06.198
I'm leaving you with all the tools

40:06.198 --> 40:08.940
to get this place back to
where you want it to go.

40:08.940 --> 40:10.434
I do wanna ask you one thing.

40:10.434 --> 40:11.267
- Sure.

40:11.267 --> 40:12.934
- Is there anything
that's happened this week

40:12.934 --> 40:14.362
that you're not happy with?

40:14.362 --> 40:16.362
- Yes, I had expected the
Blumen's room to be done,

40:16.362 --> 40:17.388
not the Koenig.

40:17.388 --> 40:19.757
It was the room I didn't expect.

40:19.757 --> 40:22.024
- And the room that we've done-

40:22.024 --> 40:23.612
- Is amazing.
- Still has problems.

40:23.612 --> 40:25.746
- Can I just tell you
something really important?

40:25.746 --> 40:27.702
This is not a makeover show.

40:27.702 --> 40:29.068
- I know that.
- Yeah.

40:29.068 --> 40:30.796
- But you're complaining about-

40:30.796 --> 40:32.412
- I wasn't saying I didn't love that room.

40:32.412 --> 40:34.471
- It'd be a great shame for
you to sound ungrateful.

40:34.471 --> 40:35.890
- Oh, I'm not ungrateful.

40:35.890 --> 40:36.938
I am just so shocked-

40:36.938 --> 40:39.744
- From the new management system to Dave,

40:39.744 --> 40:40.775
you've got no idea-

40:40.775 --> 40:42.481
- I'm coming across wrong if you think

40:42.481 --> 40:45.084
that I'm being ungrateful,
'cause I'm really not.

40:45.084 --> 40:46.737
- It sounds like that.

40:46.737 --> 40:47.729
- No.

40:47.729 --> 40:48.692
Not at all.

40:48.692 --> 40:50.218
- I can't come in and wave a magic wand

40:50.218 --> 40:51.781
and transform 15 bedrooms

40:51.781 --> 40:53.153
and put a brand-new kitchen.

40:53.153 --> 40:55.203
You now know what needs to happen.

40:55.203 --> 40:56.036
- I do.

40:56.036 --> 40:57.498
- But I need to tell you something

40:57.498 --> 40:58.904
that you're not gonna like.

40:58.904 --> 41:01.010
I arranged for a new stove...

41:01.010 --> 41:01.993
- You did?

41:01.993 --> 41:04.603
- To come, and then
when I got the engineer

41:04.603 --> 41:07.397
to come and survey the
place, unfortunately,

41:07.397 --> 41:10.985
he had to leave, because he
was gonna shut the place down,

41:10.985 --> 41:13.436
'cause there's practises that
are taking place in there

41:13.436 --> 41:14.791
that aren't appropriate.

41:14.791 --> 41:16.743
- You're saying the gas systems or...

41:16.743 --> 41:18.398
- The whole setup underneath there.

41:18.398 --> 41:20.248
Nothing's been changed in 13 years.

41:20.248 --> 41:23.862
And it's on the verge
of running illegally.

41:23.862 --> 41:26.000
- Okay.
- Mm-hmm.

41:26.000 --> 41:28.206
- Listen, I came here to help,

41:28.206 --> 41:30.192
but you need to help yourselves

41:30.192 --> 41:33.789
and dig deep and stick together, okay?

41:33.789 --> 41:35.004
Thank you.

41:35.004 --> 41:36.003
- Thank you.

41:36.003 --> 41:36.935
- Good luck.

41:36.935 --> 41:38.384
- Okay.
- Thank you, Gordon.

41:38.384 --> 41:39.217
- Okay.

41:39.217 --> 41:40.050
Good night.

41:40.050 --> 41:41.633
- Thank you.

41:41.633 --> 41:44.210
Auf wiedersehen.
- Safe travelling.

41:44.210 --> 41:45.579
(exhales deeply)

41:45.579 --> 41:47.579
- Man, that's hard work.

41:54.153 --> 41:55.782
(upbeat music)

41:55.782 --> 41:58.490
Soon after I left, Lisa
and Jonathan reverted

41:58.490 --> 41:59.775
to the old Vienna...

41:59.775 --> 42:02.044
- [Lisa] This is something
that belongs here.

42:02.044 --> 42:03.930
That came with the house.

42:03.930 --> 42:05.540
- What are you doing?

42:05.540 --> 42:06.616
You're insane.

42:06.616 --> 42:08.227
- [Gordon] By changing the decor

42:08.227 --> 42:10.034
and bringing back the original menu.

42:10.034 --> 42:11.399
- It's worse than it was.

42:11.399 --> 42:12.516
It looks horrible.

42:12.516 --> 42:14.051
- [Gordon] They chose
not to take my advice

42:14.051 --> 42:15.459
about running the inn properly...

42:15.459 --> 42:16.661
- [Lisa] Listen to me about what should be

42:16.661 --> 42:17.914
going on in the kitchen.

42:17.914 --> 42:18.953
- [Gordon] And as a result,

42:18.953 --> 42:22.453
their reputation in town remains the same.

42:56.574 --> 42:59.657
- [Announcer] One potato, two potato.
